    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, then squeeze your <strong>sausage meat</strong> from the skins into the pan (clean hands is the best way!) and discard the skins</p><p>Break the <strong>sausage meat</strong> up into bite-sized pieces with a wooden spoon and cook for 5-7 min or until the onion has softened and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, then cook for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortiglioni</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sausage meat is cooked, add the <strong>halved tomatoes </strong>and <strong>fennel seeds </strong>(not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!) to the pan with your <strong>dried oregano</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes have begun to break down</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato stock </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for a further 4-5 min or until the sauce has slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has slightly thickened, add the <strong>drained tortiglioni </strong>to the pan with a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Cook for a final 1-2 min or until the sauce begins to coat the pasta</p><p>Tip: If your pasta is looking a little dry, add another splash of starchy water!</p><p>Stir through the <strong>chopped basil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomatoey sausage & fennel tortiglioni</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/tomatoey-sausage-and-fennel-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>tomatoey sausage & fennel tortiglioni</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
